            <para>
                <emph type="bold">PROBLEM</emph>
            </para>
            <para>The toggle on shift knob is broken.</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">WHAT TO DO</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before disconnecting air lines, drain air tanks.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Disconnect airlines from knob by pushing up on the quick connect fittings and pulling down on
                        the air line (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove bezel cap and gasket, nut, lock washer, washer and then remove knob from lever (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove upper knob isolator (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove two screws from inside upper knob (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Separate upper and lower knob and remove broken toggle (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Care must be taken when removing the upper poppet, spring, lower poppet and broken toggle
                        because they can drop out easily.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If the poppets and spring have come out, place the upper poppet (the larger of the two
                        poppets) into upper knob with spring and lower poppet assembled to it (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Place the new toggle (201-999-10) into upper knob (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Reassemble in reverse order from the way it was disassembled.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Torque nut to 45 ft-lbs. (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9713011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
